cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper investigates ground-aerial uplink communication in cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper utilizes non-orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) protocol, which is a topic of interest in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the optimization of UAV trajectory and UAV-GBS association order, which involves control and system theory. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an iterative UAV trajectory design using successive convex approximation (SCA) technique, which is a machine learning optimization method. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper involves the use of a rotary-wing unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV), which is a topic of interest in robotics.
